1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:54,250
[Low Frequency]

3
00:01:47,180 --> 00:01:48,690
-Wait.
-Okay.

4
00:01:52,229 --> 00:01:54,060
Are you really going to eat with Ton?

5
00:01:56,660 --> 00:01:57,430
Yes.

6
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:02,810
I'm confused. What's going on?

7
00:02:05,410 --> 00:02:08,289
He just wanted to treat me to a meal to show his gratitude.

8
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,960
Why would he treat you to dinner when the job is not even done?

9
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,160
And you agreed?

10
00:02:15,230 --> 00:02:18,880
Yeah, this is a rare opportunity.

11
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:23,260
Then how are you going to investigate?

12
00:02:23,770 --> 00:02:25,640
Are you going to search his bag or steal his phone?

13
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:32,920
Well, I haven't told you where he asked me out for dinner.

14
00:02:34,060 --> 00:02:34,960
Where?

15
00:02:50,070 --> 00:02:51,270
Excuse me.

16
00:02:53,570 --> 00:02:54,410
Excuse me.

17
00:02:54,940 --> 00:02:56,579
Come in.

18
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:01,530
Wait over there, Mr. Mon.

19
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,680
I'll make you something delicious.

20
00:03:04,790 --> 00:03:05,880
Okay, Mr. Ton.

21
00:03:34,950 --> 00:03:37,430
We took this photo when we were still close.

22
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,530
I don't think this is going to work.

23
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:43,020
I can't find anything.

24
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:45,130
I don't understand what you're looking for.

25
00:03:46,710 --> 00:03:50,360
I'm looking for receipts, photos

26
00:03:50,380 --> 00:03:53,190
or any other evidence that can prove

27
00:03:53,230 --> 00:03:55,920
that he was close to the crime scene that day.

28
00:04:00,990 --> 00:04:03,060
But we all keep our photos on the phone now.

29
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:08,080
I searched online, but I couldn't find anything.

30
00:04:08,450 --> 00:04:11,170
So I think it should be with him.

31
00:04:15,510 --> 00:04:17,480
I don't think it'll work.

32
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:20,320
Let's go home, you don’t need to eat with him.

33
00:04:20,410 --> 00:04:22,960
What if he poisoned the food?

34
00:04:25,370 --> 00:04:27,390
Are you worried or jealous?

35
00:04:30,030 --> 00:04:31,630
Well...

36
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:33,250
It’s both.

37
00:04:35,590 --> 00:04:39,270
Don't worry. I'm leaving soon. Just for a moment.

38
00:04:39,570 --> 00:04:41,030
Are you leaving, Mr. Mon?

39
00:04:44,490 --> 00:04:45,470
Oh.

40
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:49,170
It's okay. I’m about to have a meeting.

41
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,560
But it’ll be a while.

42
00:04:51,460 --> 00:04:53,230
The dishes are ready.

43
00:04:54,010 --> 00:04:55,560
Have a taste.

44
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,540
Okay.

45
00:05:09,810 --> 00:05:11,970
Ai, what are you doing here?

46
00:05:12,510 --> 00:05:13,500
Mark.

47
00:05:14,350 --> 00:05:15,800
I should be the one asking you.

48
00:05:16,030 --> 00:05:17,290
What are you doing here?

49
00:05:17,890 --> 00:05:19,190
Why are you following me?

50
00:05:19,790 --> 00:05:20,950
Are you a stalker?

51
00:05:24,940 --> 00:05:28,300
Ai, didn’t you promise me you wouldn't do it again?

52
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:31,260
Can you stay out of this?

53
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,590
Sorry, Mr. Mark.

54
00:05:36,940 --> 00:05:38,970
Ai has something to do.

55
00:05:42,140 --> 00:05:43,230
We'll get going.

56
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:56,940
-Thank you for the food.
-Let's eat.

57
00:06:09,410 --> 00:06:10,540
It's delicious.

58
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:13,320
-Try some more.
-I want some tomatoes.

59
00:06:14,410 --> 00:06:16,360
How is it? Is it good?

60
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:20,270
It's so good.

61
00:06:22,470 --> 00:06:24,190
Tell me if that’s not enough.

62
00:06:24,220 --> 00:06:26,010
I've cooked a lot for you.

63
00:06:29,150 --> 00:06:33,220
Actually, it’s already an honor that I get to taste the food

64
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:35,140
cooked by a top global chef like Mr. Ton.

65
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:38,960
What are you talking about? That’s nothing.

66
00:06:39,090 --> 00:06:42,450
I offered to treat you as a “thank you” myself.

67
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:49,250
I have something to ask you too.

68
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:52,500
You said you'd buy me a meal to thank me.

69
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:55,730
The renovation of your house hasn't finished yet.

70
00:06:56,050 --> 00:06:57,159
What do you want to thank me for?

71
00:07:01,530 --> 00:07:02,530
Well,

72
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:06,010
I have a favor to ask you.

73
00:07:11,860 --> 00:07:14,310
Can you come into this room with me?

74
00:07:17,450 --> 00:07:18,190
Okay.

75
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,690
Come in, Mr. Mon.

76
00:07:41,159 --> 00:07:42,700
Okay.

77
00:07:44,590 --> 00:07:46,860
Do you remember this room?

78
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:50,310
Yes.

79
00:07:50,409 --> 00:07:54,710
It’s the second bedroom that you wanted to make the guest room.

80
00:07:56,220 --> 00:07:58,180
Yes, but actually,

81
00:07:58,290 --> 00:08:01,470
I didn't mean to leave this room to the guests.

82
00:08:03,130 --> 00:08:05,570
I’m going to make it…

83
00:08:12,710 --> 00:08:14,510
My daughter's bedroom.

84
00:08:18,940 --> 00:08:21,630
-Your daughter's room?
-Yes.

85
00:08:21,990 --> 00:08:25,260
But I can't tell you this in the office.

86
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:29,590
Why?

87
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:32,730
Because Mr. Yak knows my family.

88
00:08:33,110 --> 00:08:37,350
I've been secretly married in Italy for a while.

89
00:08:37,380 --> 00:08:40,370
But I didn't dare to tell my family.

90
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,030
This is beyond my expectation.

91
00:08:45,380 --> 00:08:46,950
What do you mean?

92
00:08:47,330 --> 00:08:49,180
I mean...

93
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:55,840
I didn't expect someone like Mr. Ton to hide something.

94
00:08:56,990 --> 00:09:00,460
My family has planned it for me. After I graduate,

95
00:09:00,590 --> 00:09:05,050
I'm supposed to marry someone

96
00:09:05,070 --> 00:09:06,990
from a family that my mother knows.

97
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:10,020
But now that things have already happened,

98
00:09:11,260 --> 00:09:13,700
I don't know how to tell my family about them.

99
00:09:16,590 --> 00:09:18,750
Only a few family members know

100
00:09:19,340 --> 00:09:21,980
that I’m back in Thailand.

101
00:09:26,710 --> 00:09:28,500
If that's the case,

102
00:09:29,060 --> 00:09:31,110
why are you telling me this?

103
00:09:31,900 --> 00:09:34,060
You know that I know Thames

104
00:09:34,810 --> 00:09:36,580
and also your relatives.

105
00:09:39,740 --> 00:09:42,190
I really like your work.

106
00:09:42,570 --> 00:09:44,220
And I think that one day,

107
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:46,520
I have to tell everyone about this.

108
00:09:46,650 --> 00:09:48,160
I just don't know how to say it.

109
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:50,360
I think today is a good opportunity.

110
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,650
So I'll start by telling you.

111
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:59,250
Aren't you afraid I'll tell this to your family?

112
00:10:00,610 --> 00:10:02,380
I have come to this stage.

113
00:10:02,510 --> 00:10:04,420
What will happen will happen.

114
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:10,520
If that’s the case,

115
00:10:11,490 --> 00:10:12,680
you can rest assured.

116
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:15,420
I won't tell anyone.

117
00:10:17,010 --> 00:10:18,770
Thank you very much.

118
00:10:19,850 --> 00:10:24,960
I'll design this room beautifully.

119
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:29,400
Thank you for everything.

120
00:10:30,610 --> 00:10:32,120
It’s my pleasure.

121
00:10:36,210 --> 00:10:37,690
Mr. Mon, wait!

122
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:24,820
I'll wait for you outside.

123
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:44,380
Thames.

124
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:46,250
What?

125
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:50,560
I'm sorry.

126
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,930
I won't forgive you.

127
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:58,720
I know you don't want to see me.

128
00:11:59,390 --> 00:12:00,580
But you still showed up anyway.

129
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:07,290
But I really don't understand

130
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:10,350
why I did so many bad things to you at that time.

131
00:12:18,740 --> 00:12:20,020
To be honest,

132
00:12:22,370 --> 00:12:26,080
I wanted to apologize and talk to you about this.

133
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:31,160
But when I saw you at the mall that day,

134
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,520
I couldn't say it.

135
00:12:35,850 --> 00:12:37,100
When I want to tell you now,

136
00:12:38,870 --> 00:12:40,630
you are unconscious and lying here quietly.

137
00:12:41,950 --> 00:12:44,030
I'm such a coward.

138
00:12:54,270 --> 00:12:55,620
When you wake up,

139
00:12:56,310 --> 00:12:58,180
I’ll come to apologize to you again.

140
00:12:59,510 --> 00:13:00,880
But you have to wake up first.

141
00:13:06,810 --> 00:13:07,630
Okay?

142
00:13:08,610 --> 00:13:09,340
Thames.

143
00:13:10,850 --> 00:13:12,130
Do you remember?

144
00:13:13,490 --> 00:13:16,320
I almost burned the kitchen

145
00:13:17,970 --> 00:13:20,600
when we cooked at our aunt’s house.

146
00:13:23,130 --> 00:13:26,080
Who would have thought I'd become a chef now?

147
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:33,900
When you wake up, you must try my dishes.

148
00:13:37,420 --> 00:13:41,150
Even if you're still angry at me or hate me. Even if you won't forgive me,

149
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:44,860
you have to wake up.

150
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:49,580
I’ll treat you.

151
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,790
I'm leaving.

152
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,070
Okay.

153
00:14:21,390 --> 00:14:22,670
I'll definitely go!

154
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:25,990
I'm going to eat up your restaurant, you jerk!

155
00:14:27,090 --> 00:14:27,980
Screw you, Ton.

156
00:14:48,130 --> 00:14:49,930
I don't think Mr. Ton is a bad guy.

157
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,010
Why are you so sure about it?

158
00:14:55,730 --> 00:14:56,860
I felt it.

159
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:02,790
How could you just leave him alone in the room with me? What if he chokes me?

160
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:05,190
I was watching.

161
00:15:08,210 --> 00:15:09,740
So you saw...

162
00:15:12,460 --> 00:15:13,670
I saw everything.

163
00:15:14,230 --> 00:15:15,930
The reconciliation of two cousins.

164
00:15:16,190 --> 00:15:18,500
Gosh, this is so awkward.

165
00:15:20,290 --> 00:15:22,260
I think Mr. Ton should be the one saying this.

166
00:15:22,810 --> 00:15:25,710
Yes, you saw how awkward I was too.

167
00:15:26,770 --> 00:15:30,360
So the brother you told me about is not Mr. Ton, right?

168
00:15:30,570 --> 00:15:31,810
How could it be him?

169
00:15:32,090 --> 00:15:33,940
I told you, my brother is dead.

170
00:15:34,210 --> 00:15:35,050
Yes.

171
00:15:35,450 --> 00:15:39,580
I thought you meant that he had been erased from your life.

172
00:15:41,970 --> 00:15:44,470
My half-brother actually died.

173
00:15:44,890 --> 00:15:47,500
Ton is my cousin.

174
00:15:50,150 --> 00:15:51,200
That's great.

175
00:15:52,110 --> 00:15:56,700
I'm glad that this accident was not caused by the hurt between your family.

176
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:06,570
-What are you looking at?
-The date.

177
00:16:16,450 --> 00:16:17,890
On the day of your accident,

178
00:16:18,410 --> 00:16:19,710
Mr. Ton wasn't in Thailand.

179
00:16:23,690 --> 00:16:24,850
Is this an old photo?

180
00:16:27,130 --> 00:16:28,610
I've confirmed with Mr. Yak.

181
00:16:29,250 --> 00:16:30,930
He really flew there once

182
00:16:31,070 --> 00:16:33,440
and came back for a meeting.

183
00:16:39,810 --> 00:16:41,520
Then maybe it's really not him.

184
00:16:46,050 --> 00:16:48,460
Mark and Ai are the only ones left.

185
00:17:13,380 --> 00:17:14,020
Hi.

186
00:17:16,170 --> 00:17:18,930
What have you got?

187
00:17:19,260 --> 00:17:21,579
Calm down, Mon.

188
00:17:21,650 --> 00:17:23,660
I have a lot of news, my friend.

189
00:17:23,690 --> 00:17:25,540
What is it?

190
00:17:27,260 --> 00:17:30,930
Mark went to see an actor named Ai a few days ago.

191
00:17:31,330 --> 00:17:33,440
They were in front of the hotel in the city center.

192
00:17:33,980 --> 00:17:35,690
What were they doing there?

193
00:17:35,730 --> 00:17:36,930
I don't know either.

194
00:17:37,010 --> 00:17:39,840
I saw them part after saying goodbye.

195
00:17:41,410 --> 00:17:42,760
What's next?

196
00:17:44,130 --> 00:17:46,140
Nothing happened that day.

197
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:48,320
-Mark went home to sleep.
-What?

198
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:51,940
You said you had a lot of news. That’s all you got?

199
00:17:52,370 --> 00:17:54,740
Mon, the important part is what happened after that.

200
00:17:55,690 --> 00:17:58,140
When Mark doesn't have a job,

201
00:17:58,170 --> 00:18:00,570
he likes to sleep at 4 a.m. and gets up at 10 a.m.

202
00:18:00,900 --> 00:18:03,050
He doesn't like to take a shower before going to bed.

203
00:18:03,180 --> 00:18:05,950
And he always brings liquor home.

204
00:18:06,060 --> 00:18:10,440
If you dig into his trash can, you'll find that he likes instant food.

205
00:18:10,810 --> 00:18:12,650
He doesn't have a water filter at home.

206
00:18:12,730 --> 00:18:14,880
And he likes to buy many bottles of water at once.

207
00:18:15,210 --> 00:18:18,790
Usually, he doesn't wear clothes according to the lucky color.

208
00:18:19,170 --> 00:18:21,570
And every time he goes out,

209
00:18:21,610 --> 00:18:23,830
-he likes to drive the car with the number…
-Wait.

210
00:18:24,730 --> 00:18:26,890
-What did you look into?
-How was it?

211
00:18:26,890 --> 00:18:28,240
It's so detailed.

212
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:35,120
I haven't mentioned his favorite water brand and his favorite food yet.

213
00:18:35,140 --> 00:18:38,340
Were you there to investigate or to be a stalker? You know him so well.

214
00:18:39,420 --> 00:18:42,190
That's because you told me to investigate it thoroughly.

215
00:18:42,270 --> 00:18:44,700
I asked my dad's subordinate to watch his house

216
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:46,930
and followed him 24 hours a day.

217
00:18:47,790 --> 00:18:48,960
It's too detailed.

218
00:18:49,830 --> 00:18:51,570
But I don't need it at all.

219
00:18:56,170 --> 00:18:59,260
Were you expecting me to break into his house? That's all I got.

220
00:19:02,110 --> 00:19:03,670
By the way, Mon.

221
00:19:03,690 --> 00:19:05,730
Perhaps the secret is in his house?

222
00:19:09,360 --> 00:19:10,950
-Should I get inside?
-Uh.

223
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,240
I'm just kidding.

224
00:19:13,540 --> 00:19:15,180
Don't do that.

225
00:19:18,830 --> 00:19:22,140
I don't want you to get famous for breaking into a celebrity’s house.

226
00:19:22,390 --> 00:19:25,270
Mon, trust me. I think we should get inside.

227
00:19:29,110 --> 00:19:30,570
No, please.

228
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:49,120
Where did you get my number?

229
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:51,870
Well...

230
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:58,560
Thames gave it to me before the accident.

231
00:19:59,300 --> 00:20:00,280
Thames?

232
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:03,830
Forget it.

233
00:20:04,820 --> 00:20:06,360
So what do you want to talk about?

234
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:10,590
Well...

235
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:13,520
I’m working with Thames’s manager.

236
00:20:14,670 --> 00:20:17,320
I want to talk to you

237
00:20:18,610 --> 00:20:21,630
about the night of Thames’s accident.

238
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:27,860
But the police said it was an accident.

239
00:20:32,300 --> 00:20:36,700
But maybe that's not the truth.

240
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:46,240
Are you suspecting that someone staged the accident

241
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:48,000
and framed Thames?

242
00:20:50,990 --> 00:20:53,460
This is real life, not a movie.

243
00:20:58,100 --> 00:20:59,980
I'm not sure

244
00:21:01,620 --> 00:21:02,910
about that accident.

245
00:21:04,820 --> 00:21:05,850
But

246
00:21:07,460 --> 00:21:09,540
I believe that someone

247
00:21:10,230 --> 00:21:11,700
must have framed him.

248
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,480
Let me put it this way.

249
00:21:18,070 --> 00:21:19,460
I’ve got some evidence.

250
00:21:23,060 --> 00:21:24,620
What do you want from me?

251
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:29,970
I just want to know what happened

252
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,990
after you quarrelled with Thames that night.

253
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,670
You're not suspecting

254
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:42,170
that I was the one behind it, right?

255
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:46,980
That depends on your answer.

256
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:04,330
After I quarrelled with Thames that night,

257
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:08,570
he left.

258
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:11,100
So did Ai.

259
00:22:13,610 --> 00:22:15,400
I was extremely drunk.

260
00:22:16,360 --> 00:22:19,820
When I woke up again, I was already at home.

261
00:22:23,230 --> 00:22:24,010
That's all.

262
00:22:29,380 --> 00:22:30,550
Well,

263
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:32,490
can I ask you something?

264
00:22:33,340 --> 00:22:36,100
What were you arguing about with Thames?

265
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:38,570
Are you a detective or what?

266
00:22:40,430 --> 00:22:41,960
I just want to know.

267
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:46,240
It's about the terrible things he did to me.

268
00:22:49,030 --> 00:22:50,000
What was it?

269
00:22:55,490 --> 00:22:57,000
You don’t need to know.

270
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:01,400
You just need to know that he's a jerk.

271
00:23:08,040 --> 00:23:10,810
To be honest, I don't want him to wake up.

272
00:23:19,340 --> 00:23:20,530
Is that all?

273
00:23:22,540 --> 00:23:24,240
I'll get back to work.

274
00:23:25,060 --> 00:23:26,760
Uh, okay.

275
00:23:49,690 --> 00:23:52,290
